<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2100] [EC2] Adjust fs.file-max</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2100</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From Robert Gibbon up on hbase-user@:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maybe you are running Red Hat? Just changing limits.conf I think won&apos;t&lt;br/&gt;
work because RH has a maximum total open files across the whole system,&lt;br/&gt;
which is 4096 by default, unless you do something like this too&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;echo &quot;32768&quot; &amp;gt; /proc/sys/fs/file-max&lt;br/&gt;
service network restart&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To make it permanent edit /etc/sysctl.conf to include the line:&lt;br/&gt;
     fs.file-max = 32768&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Update the remote init script appropriately. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
